article.headline: Wagner 69, Robert Morris 65
article.story: CORAOPOLIS, Pa. (AP) -- Mark Porter had 15 of his 17 points in the second half as Wagner defeated Robert Morris 69-65 Thursday night in the quarterfinals of the Northeast Conference tournament. The Seahawks (12-16), who trailed by two at halftime, shot 56 percent from the field in the second half while limiting the Colonials (14-15) to 42 percent after halftime. Sean Munson had 15 points and Durell Vinson 12 for Wagner, which has won 10 of 11 after starting the season 2-15. Porter shot 6 for 8 from the field in the second half and added game-highs in rebounds and assists with nine of each. The Seahawks outscored Robert Morris in the paint, 38-14. Senior Chaz McCrommon, who led the Colonials in scoring during the regular season with 16.9 points per game, was only 4 of 17 for 13 points. Mark Anderson had 18 points and seven rebounds and Tony Lee 12 points and eight rebounds for Robert Morris, which was the conference tournament's No. 3 seed. The No. 6 seed Seahawks advance to play top-seeded Monmouth, N.J., in the NEC semifinals on Sunday at Monmouth. Monmouth beat Central Connecticut State 54-53 Thursday night.
